    Pole work clinic - 13th February

    Friday 13 February 2026
    15:00 - 19:00
    Chimneys (near Moreton-in-Marsh, GL56 9QU)

    A comprehensive polework clinic with sessions for all levels. Pole work is the perfect way to improve your horse's agility, balance, and coordination...all while having a blast! Our clinic is designed to cater to riders of all levels, with exercises tailored to suit your individual needs and goals. The sessions will be good for: - getting young horses out to a different venue - strengthening horses coming back into work - make a change for dressage horses - improve rider balance and accuracy - rideability training for jumping horses Each session will include 3 to 4 horses of a similar level to ensure that everyone gets the most out of it.

    Arena Eventing at Rectory Farm

    Saturday 28 February 2026
    12:00 - 17:00
    Rectory Farm, Cirencester GL7 7JW

    This clinic will help riders improve control, confidence, and rideability over a course of show jumps and XC-style fences in an enclosed arena setting. Youll work on building a balanced, adjustable canter, riding accurate lines, and maintaining control before and after fences. The focus is on rhythm, straightness, and decision-making, rather than speed. Exercises will help you understand how to set your horse up properly, use your aids more effectively, and make clearer plans between fences. The clinic is suitable for riders who want to improve their jumping technique, feel more confident riding courses, and develop skills that transfer directly to cross-country and show jumping. Fences will be adapted to suit the level of the group, with plenty of feedback and clear explanations throughout. Expect a supportive, structured session with a strong emphasis on correct basics and practical exercises!

    from 60

    Expert Training in Oxfordshire

    My group clinics offer specialised training in show jumping, polework, and cross country. These single-day sessions welcome riders from beginner to advanced levels, whether you ride for pleasure or competition.

    Each clinic focuses on the Dan Bizzarro Method, combining technical instruction with practical application. With small group sizes, you receive personalised feedback while benefiting from watching fellow riders tackle similar challenges.

    My clinics cater to both amateur riders building confidence and competitors preparing for events. From foundational polework clinics to advanced show-jumping and cross country sessions, there's a clinic designed for your goals.

    What's Included

    • Single-day training sessions for all levels
    • Show-jumping, polework, and cross country options
    • Small group sizes for individual attention
    • Suitable for amateur riders and competitors
    • Competition preparation and confidence building
    • Expert instruction from international eventing coach
